In addition to the current high death toll of 1,121 victims, the severe economic impacts are being assessed.
Petroleum and chemicals produced in the Gulf region were sharply reduced as was oil and natural gas extraction.
The 0.1% rise was extremely below economic forecasts.
Farming losses are expected to be $900 million.
Part of the economic impact of Katrina is the unemployment rate in Louisiana which has risen to 11.5%.
The U.S. House of Representatives unanimously passed a $6.1 billion tax assistance package for people and businesses displaced due to Katrina and sent it to the U.S. Senate for consideration.
